<item>
            <title>[LU-6995] incorrect use of bvec_iter_page in dio_complete_routine</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6995</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;bvec_iter_page is expecting a biovecs list as a first argument, not a biovec. That works as long as there is only one biovec in the bio. If there is more than one, then invalid memory is dereferences since bvl is a single vector, not a list. This only affect 3.14+ kernels, where HAVE_BVEC_ITER is true. Don&apos;t use bvec_iter_page, but create the right macro to simply return the vector&apos;s bv_page. Bug introduced in commit 833b670a.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
